Mashpee ADU Laws: Size: ADUs can be up to 900 square feet and cannot be less than 350 square feet. 
Provisions: ADUs must be self-contained with separate sleeping, cooking, and sanitary facilities. 
Bedrooms: ADUs can have a maximum of two bedrooms. 
Design Consistency: The design of the ADU must be consistent with the existing dwelling. 
Parking: At least one off-street parking space is required for the ADU, but no new curb cuts or driveways are permitted. 
Occupancy & Rental: While the bylaw generally allows for renting either the primary dwelling or the ADU, both cannot be rented simultaneously, and rental periods must be at least 30 consecutive days, though a 12-month rental requirement for year-round housing was considered by the Mashpee Planning Board, according to CapeNews.net. 
Owner-Occupancy: The property owner must reside in either the primary dwelling or the ADU. 
Other Requirements: Compliance with wastewater treatment, conservation commission, and historic requirements is necessary.
